

MAKAPILI

   Tawag sa taksil sa sariling kababayan o kaibigan.
   Referring to a traitor to one’s countrymen or friends.

   From the Makabayang Katipunan ng mga Pilipino (Patriotic Association of
   Filipinos) who during the Japanese occupation of the Philippines in the
   1940s provided assistance to Japan’s military.

   The Spanish-derived Filipino word for “traitor” is traydor.
